 data-end=\"782\"><a href=\"https:\/\/w3techs.com\/technologies\/overview\/content_management\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong data-start=\"435\" data-end=\"486\">WordPress powers 43.2% of all websites globally<\/strong><\/a> and commands a <strong data-start=\"502\" data-end=\"565\">market share of over 63.1% among content management systems<\/strong>\u2014more than all its competitors combined, including Wix, Joomla, Drupal, and Shopify. This dominance is not accidental; it reflects years of continuous innovation, security upgrades, and a thriving developer community.<\/p>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"784\" data-end=\"1083\">Over <a href=\"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/about\/stats\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong data-start=\"789\" data-end=\"813\">810 million websites<\/strong><\/a> rely on WordPress for publishing, business, e-commerce and more. From global enterprises like Sony Music and The Walt Disney Company to local brands and public institutions, WordPress is trusted to deliver scalable, secure and high-performance websites at every level.<\/p>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1085\" data-end=\"1153\">For businesses in Kenya, this means working with a platform that is:<\/p>\n<ul data-start=\"1155\" data-end=\"1398\">\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1155\" data-end=\"1198\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1157\" data-end=\"1198\">Globally proven and locally adaptable<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1199\" data-end=\"1265\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1201\" data-end=\"1265\">Backed by thousands of developers, plugins, and integrations<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1266\" data-end=\"1337\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1268\" data-end=\"1337\">Flexible enough for small websites and enterprise-level platforms<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1338\" data-end=\"1398\">\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1340\" data-end=\"1398\">Supported by regular core updates and security patches<\/p>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1400\" data-end=\"1592\">At Aminifu Digital, we harness this robust foundation to build custom WordPress websites that are not only SEO-ready and mobile-friendly but also designed to scale as your organisation grows.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"610\" data-end=\"662\"><strong data-start=\"614\" data-end=\"662\">Flexible for Both SMEs and Large Enterprises<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"664\" data-end=\"1094\">WordPress is highly customisable, allowing businesses to scale as they grow. SMEs benefit from quick-to-launch websites with minimal overheads, while larger enterprises and institutions can implement complex, multi-site setups or powerful custom features using bespoke themes and plugins. At Aminifu Digital Agency, we build everything from straightforward corporate sites to large, multilingual publishing platforms\u2014all on WordPress.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1096\" data-end=\"1138\"><strong data-start=\"1100\" data-end=\"1138\">Easy to Manage, No Coding Required<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1140\" data-end=\"1477\">With WordPress, your internal teams don\u2019t need to be tech experts to update content, upload blogs, or make basic site edits. The dashboard is intuitive and user-friendly. We provide training after every project to ensure your team can manage the site with confidence, reducing your reliance on external developers for day-to-day updates.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1479\" data-end=\"1542\"><strong data-start=\"1483\" data-end=\"1542\">A Massive Ecosystem of Themes, Plugins and Integrations<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1544\" data-end=\"1815\">From e-commerce plugins like WooCommerce to SEO tools such as Rank Math and Yoast, WordPress has a vast ecosystem that makes almost any integration possible. Need to integrate payments, CRMs, or third-party APIs? We\u2019ll ensure you get a secure and seamless implementation.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1817\" data-end=\"1867\"><strong data-start=\"1821\" data-end=\"1867\">Open-Source, Secure and Constantly Updated<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1869\" data-end=\"2210\">WordPress is backed by a massive global community of developers who actively maintain and improve its codebase. With regular updates and robust security best practices, it offers a future-proof foundation for websites in every industry. Our agency ensures all themes and plugins are kept updated, secure, and compliant with modern standards.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221;]<\/p>\n<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"115\" data-end=\"168\"><strong data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"168\">Common Mistakes Businesses Make with WordPress<\/strong><\/h2>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"448\">While WordPress is powerful, flexible and easy to use, many businesses in Kenya unknowingly make decisions that hurt performance, SEO and user experience. At Aminifu Digital Agency, we often encounter underperforming WordPress sites that were built quickly, with little technical planning. These issues are common among businesses attempting DIY or low-cost WordPress development in Kenya without strategic planning or technical oversight.<\/p>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"450\" data-end=\"491\">Here are the most common mistakes we see:<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"493\" data-end=\"553\"><strong data-start=\"497\" data-end=\"553\">1. Choosing Bloated Themes That Slow Down Load Times<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"555\" data-end=\"899\">Many off-the-shelf WordPress themes come with unnecessary features, scripts and design elements that aren\u2019t needed. These slow down your site\u2014leading to poor user experience and lower rankings on search engines. Research shows that <strong data-start=\"787\" data-end=\"849\">a 1-second delay in load time can reduce conversions by 7%<\/strong>, and Google considers speed a key ranking factor.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"901\" data-end=\"958\"><strong data-start=\"905\" data-end=\"958\">2. Overusing Drag-and-Drop Builders That Harm SEO<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"960\" data-end=\"1234\">Page builders like Elementor and WPBakery are convenient but often generate bloated code and unnecessary scripts. While they\u2019re useful for prototyping, over-reliance on them can reduce site speed and harm technical SEO. Clean, custom-coded pages load faster and rank better.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1236\" data-end=\"1295\"><strong data-start=\"1240\" data-end=\"1295\">3. Installing Insecure Plugins and Ignoring Backups<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1297\" data-end=\"1546\">The WordPress plugin ecosystem is massive, but not all plugins are maintained or secure. We\u2019ve seen sites hacked due to outdated or poorly coded plugins. Without regular backups or malware scanning in place, recovery becomes difficult and expensive.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1548\" data-end=\"1592\"><strong data-start=\"1552\" data-end=\"1592\">4. Neglecting Technical Optimisation<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1594\" data-end=\"1852\">A fast, SEO-ready WordPress site isn\u2019t just about content\u2014it needs schema markup, proper caching, minified scripts, image optimisation, and an XML sitemap. Many sites skip these essentials, which limits their discoverability and visibility on search engines.<\/p>\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1854\" data-end=\"1888\"><strong data-start=\"1858\" data-end=\"1888\">5. Poor Mobile Performance<\/strong><\/h3>\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1890\" data-end=\"2116\">Over 90% of internet users in Kenya access websites via mobile. Yet many WordPress sites are not properly optimised for mobile responsiveness, loading times, or touch usability\u2014resulting in high bounce rates and lost business.<\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/